article.headline: CS Bakersfield 61, San Jose St. 55
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- Alex Johnson scored 13 points and hit a trio of timely 3-pointers to lead Cal State Bakersfield past San Jose State 61-55 Monday. Bakersfield (5-12) led by 12 at halftime and withstood a late run from San Jose State, which scored only five first-half field goals but shot 52 percent in the second half. DaShawn Wright led San Jose State (7-8) with 17 points and Robert Owens added 12. Santwon Latunde had 12 points and nine rebounds for Bakersfield, which led 29-17 at halftime and withstood several San Jose State rallies. The Spartans mounted a 6-0 run to pull within 44-38 midway through the second half, but Johnson answered with a 3 with 8:57 left. The lead was whittled back to six with 2:58 left before Bakersfield scored five straight points.
